          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-4185 llite: Revise create with no open optimization.",
        "message": "LU-4185 llite: Revise create with no open optimization.\n\nCurrently ll_lookup_nd just returns a negative when\nwe are trying to create something with no open (read mkdir).\nThis is all fine most of the cases, except if the directory\nwhere we are trying to do it is not writeable by us.\nIn that case vfs_create would return EPERM seeing as how\na negative dentry means the create cannot proceed.\nBut in reality if there is an existing name there that\nwe just did not have cached, the proper return is EEXIST that\ncould only happen if we did do the lookup.\n\nSo amend the optimization to only take place if the\ndirectory is writeable by us, otherwise do the full lookup.\n\nChange-Id: I5d5125f00c9a21d46a7c39331d06d53e6b717ca6\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
